  "description": [
    "UNITED LABOR BULLETIN VOL VIII NEWS OF THE LABOR UNIONS MUSICIANS During the early part of the sum mer the Denver Musical Protective Association with the assistance of the Trades Assembly made an effort to unionise the Iris and the Isis the atres fmt without success and these two houses were declared unfair by the Trades Assembly For various reasons however thefight was not pushed until last Sunday when the Assembly took it up again and this time with the determination on the part if the musical union to carry it to a finish The managers of these two houses Messrs Baxter and Weber when attempts have been made to convert them to unionism have repeatedly stated that they did not have to employ union people to get their patronage All that could be done by talking with them Las been done and now ve are deter mined to see if it is true that union men and women of Denver will pat ronise Scab theatres after they have ibeen asked not to do so We are go ing to have watchers out to see who the union members are that patronise the enemies of unionism and the fight will"
  ],
